------------------------------------------
DYNAPHOPY 1.1
------------------------------------------
Program to calculate crystal anharmonic frequencies from molecular
dynamics calculation obtained from VASP code.

------------------------------------------
Installation instructions
------------------------------------------
1. Requirements
Python 2.6 or higher
Phonopy    (http://phonopy.sourceforge.net)
Matplotlib
Scipy
h5py

2. Download the source code and place it in the installation directory

3. Run setup.py script to install
python setup.py install --user

------------------------------------------
Executing the program
------------------------------------------
1) Script method
Create/edit script like input.py and execute it
The comments in the script makes it (hopefully) self explained.
    Example: input.py

2a) Command line method
./dynaphopy input_file vasp_MD_OUTCAR [Options]
execute ./dynaphopy -h for detailed description of available options

2b) Enter interactive interface
Use -i option
./dynaphopy input_file vasp_MD_OUTCAR -i

Input files for several compounds can be found in Example directory

